        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 24 at 2:22PM CDT until July 24 at 3:00PM CDT by NWS Chicago IL</headline>
        <description>SVRLOT

The National Weather Service in Chicago has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Northwestern Will County in northeastern Illinois...
Southern DuPage County in northeastern Illinois...
South central Cook County in northeastern Illinois...

* Until 300 PM CDT.

* At 222 PM CDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from North Aurora to near Yorkville to near Plano, moving
east at 50 mph.

HAZARD...70 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect considerable tree damage. Damage is likely to
mobile homes, roofs, and outbuildings.

* Severe thunderstorms will be near...
Wheaton, Plainfield, Warrenville, Naperville, and Aurora around
230 PM CDT.
Woodridge, Bolingbrook, Glen Ellyn, Romeoville, Joliet, Lombard,
Downers Grove, and Lisle around 235 PM CDT.
Westmont, Darien, Lemont, Oak Brook, and Clarendon Hills around
240 PM CDT.
Lockport, Homer Glen, Crest Hill, Willowbrook, Hinsdale, Willow
Springs, and Burr Ridge around 245 PM CDT.

Other locations impacted by these severe thunderstorms include
Fairmont, Crystal Lawns, Oakbrook Terrace, and York Center.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
